                                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Take a Break From the Modern Internet, Surf the Original Web]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/take-a-break-from-the-modern-internet-surf-the-original-web/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Faisal Rasool]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/a-man-sitting-cross-legged-with-a-laptop-browsing-retro-style-websites-with-a-large-vintage-cursor-pointing-at-old-school-web-pages-in-the-background.png" length="4528" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Web]]></category><category><![CDATA[internet]]></category><category><![CDATA[ai]]></category><category><![CDATA[History]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            I healed my brain rot.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Most of us feel stuck switching back and forth between the same five apps. We’re stuck because companies spend billions to keep us “engaged” on their respective platforms. That’s why the internet feels like it has shrunk to a handful of apps, and stopped being a place you once explored and browsed. The good news is, the internet of old still exists.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sun, 14 Sep 2025 21:15:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/take-a-break-from-the-modern-internet-surf-the-original-web/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[5 Console Expansion Slots That Barely Did Anything]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/console-expansion-slots-that-barely-did-anything/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Sydney Butler]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/shutterstock_2668459721.jpg" length="482" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Video Games]]></category><category><![CDATA[Retro Gaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[History]]></category><category><![CDATA[Nintendo]]></category><category><![CDATA[PlayStation]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Don't you hate it when one puzzle piece is missing?
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Console manufacturers often have lots of plans for their hardware down the road, sometimes years into the platform's lifecycle. Which is why, when you first bought a console, you may have noticed proprietary ports that have no obvious or explained purpose.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sun, 14 Sep 2025 21:01:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/console-expansion-slots-that-barely-did-anything/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[What’s New and Continuing on AMC+ in September and October]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/whats-new-and-continuing-on-amc-in-september-and-october/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Keeley Brooks]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/mixcollage-11-sep-2025-05-59-pm-3064.jpg" length="359" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Streaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[AMC+]]></category><category><![CDATA[TV Shows]]></category><category><![CDATA[ Movies]]></category><category><![CDATA[Video Streaming]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Documentaries, movies, and series, oh my!
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p><a href="https://www.amcplus.com/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">AMC+</a> has announced somewhat of a fall 2025 lineup, and it’s ripe with fresh content that you’ll want to see. From AMC+ Exclusives and Original Series to Sundance Now documentaries and spooky Shudder entries, I’m certain you’ll find something here to suit your fancy.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sun, 14 Sep 2025 20:31:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/whats-new-and-continuing-on-amc-in-september-and-october/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[The 10 Best Classic Windows Screensavers, Ranked]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/the-best-classic-windows-screensavers-ranked/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Ismar Hrnjicevic]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/09/collage-of-classic-windows-screensaver-elements-with-the-windows-95-logo-in-the-center.jpg" length="727" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Some screensavers had us glued for hours!
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Many of us have fond memories of staring endlessly at all those cool screensavers that Microsoft came up with in the 90s and early 2000s. In fact, I'd go so far as to say that these colorful animations were a core part of the early computing experience, even if many of us were too young to understand their real practical purpose.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sun, 14 Sep 2025 20:15:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/the-best-classic-windows-screensavers-ranked/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[MacOS Myth Busted: Do You Really Need to Close Apps?]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/why-i-rarely-bother-closing-my-mac-apps/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Sydney Butler]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/shutterstock_2512686033.jpg" length="533" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Mac]]></category><category><![CDATA[macOS]]></category><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[RAM]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            An open question.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>When Windows was my daily operating system, I'd developed the habit of closing programs when I wasn't using them. Especially in the early days when RAM was in short supply.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sun, 14 Sep 2025 20:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/why-i-rarely-bother-closing-my-mac-apps/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Movies with Unexpected Video Game Adaptations]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/movies-that-surprisingly-have-video-game-adaptations/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Mark McPherson]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/marlon-brando-in-a-suit-from-the-movie-the-godfather.jpg" length="251" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Streaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[ Movies]]></category><category><![CDATA[video games]]></category><category><![CDATA[Video Streaming]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            From sci-fi thrillers to mafia epics, how did these unlikely movies become playable adaptations?
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>It’s not uncommon for a movie to receive a video game adaptation, but there are certain types of films you can always expect to get such games. It’s usually a film loaded with action (<em>Goldeneye</em>) or coming from a notable franchise (<em>Batman Forever</em>). Rarely are their <a href="https://www.howtogeek.com/category/video-games/" target="_blank">video games</a> based on historical dramas or conspiracy thrillers.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sun, 14 Sep 2025 19:30:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/movies-that-surprisingly-have-video-game-adaptations/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Hatchbacks: A Dying Breed in North America's Car Market in 2025]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/the-unlikely-survival-of-a-niche-market-darling/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Brent vd Schyff]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2025_toyota_gr-corolla_premium-plus_at_supersonicred_002-1500x1000.jpg" length="269" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Automotive]]></category><category><![CDATA[Volkswagen]]></category><category><![CDATA[Toyota]]></category><category><![CDATA[Corolla]]></category><category><![CDATA[Honda]]></category><category><![CDATA[Civic Type R]]></category><category><![CDATA[Mini]]></category><category><![CDATA[John Cooper Works Coupe]]></category><category><![CDATA[BMW]]></category><category><![CDATA[Audi]]></category><category><![CDATA[Mercedes-Benz]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Once a global sensation, hatchbacks are now a rarity. Discover the surprising reasons behind their decline and whether a comeback is coming.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Please excuse the headline (or don't), but sounding the alarm and issuing the public service announcement is needed. Globally, it was a popular choice from the 60s stemming from an international oil crisis, peaking in the 90s in a widespread way, but now, hatchbacks (or rather performance hatchbacks) are all but dead, a figment of what they once were.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sun, 14 Sep 2025 19:15:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/the-unlikely-survival-of-a-niche-market-darling/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[7 Linux Distributions I Tested in the Past Year, Ranked]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/linux-distros-i-tried-in-the-past-year-ranked/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jordan Gloor]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/08/a-laptop-panel-with-several-linux-distributions-running-in-terminal-connections-and-virtual-machines.jpg" length="303" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Linux]]></category><category><![CDATA[Linux & macOS Terminal]]></category><category><![CDATA[KDE Plasma]]></category><category><![CDATA[Open Source]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Which one is missing from this list?
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Over the past year I've booted numerous Linux distributions, and seven of them I installed on bare metal and put to the test with daily use. Here are those seven distributions (also called distros) in order of worst to best experience.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sun, 14 Sep 2025 19:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/linux-distros-i-tried-in-the-past-year-ranked/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[The Korean EV That Feels More Expensive Than It Is]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/korean-ev-feels-more-expensive-than-it-is/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Adam Gray]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/09/2025-genesis-gv60-feature.jpg" length="399" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Automotive]]></category><category><![CDATA[Electric Vehicles]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            It may cost more than its siblings, but this Korean EV feels way fancier than the price tag suggests.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>The clock’s ticking—September 30 is the last day to <a href="https://www.howtogeek.com/ev-phev-tax-credit-guide-sept-30/" target="_blank">snag that sweet $7,500 federal tax credit</a> on a new EV. No wonder dealerships are moving metal faster than ever.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sun, 14 Sep 2025 18:30:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/korean-ev-feels-more-expensive-than-it-is/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[4 Touchpad Gestures That Help Me Navigate Windows Faster]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/touchpad-gestures-to-navigate-windows-faster/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Shan Abdul]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/a-person-using-the-laptop-s-touchpad.jpg" length="1668" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[Accessibility]]></category><category><![CDATA[customization]]></category><category><![CDATA[mouse]]></category><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Swipe your way through Windows!
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Did you know Windows lets you switch between apps and get around the interface using just the touchpad? This means you don’t always need to reach for the keyboard or mouse, making navigation quicker and more efficient. Let’s dive into how touchpad gestures can help you get things done faster.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sun, 14 Sep 2025 18:15:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/touchpad-gestures-to-navigate-windows-faster/</guid></item></channel>
